CatDescriptText: Possible related article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 22, 1964, pg. 22 reads: "Philly Teens Win Owens Track Test - Philadelphia - Philadelphia captured top team honors in inter-city championship Jesse Owens Olympic Development track meets at Franklin Field here Saturday, but the Quakers had down-to-the-wire competition from Boston and Baltimore, both scoring more first places than the Philadelphians. Pittsburgh was fourth...Four Pittsburgh youngsters won first place medals, in as many events.  They included Nate Rowe, in the 16-17 age bracket of the 100-yard dash; Carol Redmond, 50 yard dash winner in 16-17 department; William Parker, winner of running broad jump for 12-13 age group, and Jevona Smith, who leaped 22 feet, 1 inch in the same event, for the 16-17 age group..."
TitMainTitle: Jesse Owens presenting trophy to young man, possibly Nate Rowe or William Parker, standing at Jesse Owens Olympic Development Track Meet
